OL,6,FMiss Jarvis, who suffered from
OL,7,FAlzheimer's disease, also made Flowers
OL,8,Fexecutor of her will in 2004, leaving
OL,9,F#10,000 to her two nieces along with
OL,10,Fthe rest of her money to good causes,
OL,11,Fincluding the children's home in South
OL,12,FAfrica, the Donkey Sanctuary, guide
OL,13,Fdogs for the blind and deaf and the
OL,14,FMethodist Church's project for homes
OL,15,Ffor elderly parishioners.
OL,17,FBut Mr Allman continued: "There was an
OL,18,Faspect of Mr Flowers' life she could
OL,19,Fnot be aware of ` which was an
OL,20,Faddiction to class A drugs among other
OL,21,Fweaknesses.
