OL,6,FBy now Miss Jarvis, a once "sprightly"
OL,7,Fpensioner, had deteriorated and gone
OL,8,Finto a care home and, unable to manage
OL,9,Fher money, Flowers took control,
OL,10,Ftreating her account as his own, the
OL,11,Fcourt heard.
OL,13,FFlowers opened an account at the Co-op
OL,14,FBank for her pension from her teaching
OL,15,Fjob to be paid into, but this
OL,16,Fcontinued until long after she had
OL,17,Fdied and an investigation began,
OL,18,Fleading to discovery of the fraud.
