OL,6,F"It is a betrayal of friendship and
OL,7,Ftrust by him," Mr Elias continued, "To
OL,8,Fabuse, squander money on class A drugs
OL,9,Fto some extent and holidays and
OL,10,Fstaircases.
OL,12,Fthrown it all away, breathtaking in
OL,13,Fone sense, tragic in another, despite
OL,14,Fhis character flaws, he got as high as
OL,15,Fhe did."
OL,17,FA proceeds of crime hearing will be
OL,18,Fheld later in the year to try to
OL,19,Frecoup some of the money Flowers stole.
